{"type":"message","id":"a21f038e","parentId":"7bffa14a","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:21:58.707Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 20:21 GMT+2] OPERATION: MANUAL RESUSCITATION & BACKLOG PURGE.\n\n1.  **Recon (Sub-Agent Flash):**\n    *   *Check:* `rustc --version`, `cargo --version`.\n    *   *Decision:* If exists -> Build `src/rust_core` (maturin/cargo). If not -> Create `src/core/rust_fallback.py`.\n\n2.  **Integration (Try-Except Fallback):**\n    *   Edit `src/dmarket/api/client.py` (or where logic lives).\n    *   *Code:*\n        ```python\n        try:\n            import dmarket_rust_core as core\n            BACKEND = \"RUST\"\n        except ImportError:\n            import src.core.rust_fallback as core\n            BACKEND = \"PYTHON_LEGACY\"\n        ```\n\n3.  **Backlog Purge (Pareto):**\n    *   Overwrite `docs/AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md`.\n    *   *Content:* The 5 critical tasks specified (Rust Link, WS Stable, SHM Opt, Profit Telemetry, Error Handling).\n\n4.  **Reporting Hook (Final):**\n    *   Run `generate_final_report()`.\n    *   *Expectation:* Backend status (\"RUST\" or \"PYTHON_LEGACY\") and benchmark.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Rust status.\n    *   Fallback mechanism logic.\n    *   Top 5 Backlog."}],"timestamp":1771179718705}}
