{"type":"message","id":"c52f1a6d","parentId":"0c2640df","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:22:23.945Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Implementing the Rust Fallback**\n\nI've got the Rust compiler and Cargo missing, a critical dependency. Now, I'm focusing on the fallback mechanism. I'm creating a Python module, `src/core/rust_fallback.py`, to handle situations where Rust isn't available. Then, I'll integrate this fallback into `src/dmarket/api/client.py`.\n\n\n**Initiating the Python Fallback**\n\nI'm starting the fallback implementation. First, I'm verifying the directory structure to prepare for creating the `rust_fallback.py` file. I'll need a basic placeholder in `src/core/rust_fallback.py` to handle the missing Rust compilation. This module will be crucial for gracefully handling the absence of Rust.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771179743939_142","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Test-Path src/core"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5634,"output":164,"cacheRead":4822,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5798,"cost":{"input":0.011268,"output":0.001968,"cacheRead":0.0009644000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014200400000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771179736863}}
